#!/usr/bin/env bash
set -euo pipefail

cat <<'EOF'
Pinky Brain Protocol Contract

Runtime lanes:
- Brain/user Terminal lane: manual commands shown after the brain symbol.
- Pinky automatic lane: visible direct syntax ending in # pinky.
- Conversation continuation lane: standalone continuation signal only.

Standalone control signals:
- Narf! means Pinky automated continuation callback.
- mouse symbol means safe continuation is available.
- brain symbol means human/model decision required.
- stop symbol means hard stop.
- k or K means manual kill switch.

Strict signal rule:
- Runtime control signals must be standalone lines only.
- Prefix prose plus a signal must not match.
- Do not patch Pinky to compensate for inconsistent assistant formatting unless the protocol is intentionally redesigned and fixture-tested.

Command execution rule:
- Pinky cockpit executes only project-prefixed visible direct commands ending in # pinky.
- Human/manual commands belong in the Brain/user Terminal lane.
- High-impact actions require brain review.

Recommended status check:
cd ~/Desktop/pinky-brain && ./bin/pinky-status
EOF

Binary lane rule:
- one reply targets one operator only
- Brain lane and Pinky lane must not be mixed
- Terminal 1 is cockpit watcher
- Terminal 2 is Brain admin
